<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Selinar Crystalwind:
[B]The secret is finding a low blue in a controlled situation that doesn't hit hard.  Unfortunately, you are in the same boat I am - those weak blue mobs are just barely green (Fizz in WFP was great through 46, and plaugebone skels in DL were prefect through 47).  Problem is, in my rush to get 49, I've missed these spots.

Something that I did which wasn't *smart* but worked was this:

Get into a LGuk King group
Bind directly in front of the exit portal
Group as you normally would, and then leave when your group does.
Zone into LGuk, see if anyone is camping the King.

If not, HP buff and MR buff, zone to UGuk, and gate.  You *should* gate in out of sight of the mobs, regardless though, you should *just* have time to DB before you aggro the whole place on you.  Back against a wall, when DB fades cast DA, and the instant it fades, pop through the portal to UGuk.  

In my test of this, I took well over 150 invuln hits in the 40 seconds I was down there.  2 defense points.  Wait 15 minutes, repeat.  

Worth a shot.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
