<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Caelym</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hullo all,<P>With the recent patch that shows skills greater than master (100) I was supprised to see my defense still at 174. I don't think I've had a defense skill raise since my mid-thirties... sigh. I try (heh) to get beat on in 'safe' or controlled situations to attempt to raise my still... but no luck for about 5 levels of getting beat on...<P>I have 2 questions for you all:<P>1. What is our defense cap? Casters Realm states 175 (in which case I'm off by 1...) - however I seem to vagely recall reading that the cap was raised to 200? Is our defense capped at 175 below L50 and 200 at 50+? (or something similar)<P>2. Is going to the arena with a pet-class buddy, and getting beat-on by the blue pet a viable option for raising my defense (ie: with respect to time/effectiveness/etc)? Or should I do the 'round blues up and DA at the zone' method?<P>Thanks all,<P>Caelym<BR>L48 Cleric of Tunare<BR>Order of Oblivion<BR>Cazic Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kregar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My defense at lvl 50 just hit 181 last night, so the cap is not 175. As far as the pet thing, I was going to try it but just haven't had a chance so I have no idea. <P>------------------<BR>Kregar, 50 Priest of Innoruuk<BR>Allied Giants - Ayonae Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kandolek</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">1) our 1hb and 2hb cap at 175. Offense and defense camp at 200. (I'm at 198 currently) Always have been since the game started.  The only skill increases we get post 50 are meditate and channeling (2 per level after 50 to new max, forget what; maybe 252) <P>2) My luck in increases has always been 'the more blue mobs the better'. This of course has much more serious problems if something goes bad. From everything I've heard, the pet thing does work. It's much slower but much safer than DA'ing in a train.<P>Kandolek<BR>53 cleric on BB<BR>Seekers of Lore</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Selinar Crystalwind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The secret is finding a low blue in a controlled situation that doesn't hit hard.  Unfortunately, you are in the same boat I am - those weak blue mobs are just barely green (Fizz in WFP was great through 46, and plaugebone skels in DL were prefect through 47).  Problem is, in my rush to get 49, I've missed these spots.<P>Something that I did which wasn't *smart* but worked was this:<P>Get into a LGuk King group<BR>Bind directly in front of the exit portal<BR>Group as you normally would, and then leave when your group does.<BR>Zone into LGuk, see if anyone is camping the King.<P>If not, HP buff and MR buff, zone to UGuk, and gate.  You *should* gate in out of sight of the mobs, regardless though, you should *just* have time to DB before you aggro the whole place on you.  Back against a wall, when DB fades cast DA, and the instant it fades, pop through the portal to UGuk.  <P>In my test of this, I took well over 150 invuln hits in the 40 seconds I was down there.  2 defense points.  Wait 15 minutes, repeat.  <P>Worth a shot.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KamuelaTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">At level 50 my defense skill is 183.<P>I don't plan on doing anything to try max it.<P>I figure I will be getting beat on often enough for long enough when I hit 51 and 52 to take care of this.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">sertain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am level 49 and my defense is at 195.  From what I understand the cap is 200.  To be honest I fought inside paw and mistmoor alot from 28 or so to I would guess around 43.  Those gnolls in paw absolutely hate a heal, and so I felt I was ready for the agro changes when they were made.  I know alot of people fight in the outdoors at alot of levels (i.e. lake of ill omen, etc.), but I really learned my craft inside the dungeons.  Hopefully my defense will move again when I hit 50.<P>Sertain Crimsonpepper<BR>Cleric of the 49th Age<BR>Planes of Ayonae Ro<P>P.S.  LOL one thing people always knew that knew me was me and the pally I fought with alot had major hot keys in bright red and caps that showed a train was coming.  Fight in mistmoor and paw and u have to have these to save others.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">the cap is 200. I have 200. Of course, I used to love standing toe to toe with spectres in oasis on my road to 50+. Those guys will do wonders for your defense skill.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zakalwe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I checked mine last night, and to my shame my defense is only 198. I can't believe it hasn't gone up to 200 yet, with the amount of beatings I take on a regular basis.<P>Looks like I'm gonna have to work on this later...<BR><P>------------------<BR>Zakalwe Soulwarden<BR>Plum Templar of Rivervale<BR>Xev</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
